8
00:00:36.950 --> 00:00:41.130
You have three major tunics that surround the eye.

9
00:00:42.690 --> 00:00:46.010
So it's as if they were three socks, one inside the other.

10
00:00:46.990 --> 00:00:50.190
The first sock is called the sclera.

11
00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:55.190
It is continuous with the cornea anteriorly.

12
00:00:56.141 --> 00:00:58.041
transparent, then you have the

13
00:00:58.041 --> 00:01:00.021
limbus, then the white part.

14
00:01:00.561 --> 00:01:02.261
This is the first

15
00:01:02.261 --> 00:01:04.281
layer. I remove this first

16
00:01:04.281 --> 00:01:06.141
sock, and then, we encounter

17
00:01:06.141 --> 00:01:08.181
an important layer called the choroid.

18
00:01:08.721 --> 00:01:10.021
And the choroid,

19
00:01:10.241 --> 00:01:12.021
we see here, you see,

20
00:01:12.241 --> 00:01:13.581
which is a layer that is

21
00:01:13.581 --> 00:01:15.561
extremely vascularized.

22
00:01:15.761 --> 00:01:18.161
And this choroid continues

23
00:01:18.161 --> 00:01:19.801
anteriorly, here,

24
00:01:20.081 --> 00:01:21.541
with what is called

25
