00:01:56.562 --> 00:01:57.902
and then there will be a relationship

37
00:01:57.902 --> 00:01:59.662
with what we call the suspensory

38
00:02:00.542 --> 00:02:02.342
muscles of the iris, which we will see in detail

39
00:02:02.342 --> 00:02:04.162
later to understand their

40
00:02:04.162 --> 00:02:04.742
physiology.

41
00:02:05.842 --> 00:02:08.402
So we see the crystalline lens,

42
00:02:09.142 --> 00:02:10.502
the different chambers

43
00:02:10.502 --> 00:02:12.482
that will appear, the pupillary orifice,

44
00:02:14.202 --> 00:02:15.422
Here, a little further,

45
00:02:16.402 --> 00:02:17.842
in this choroid

46
00:02:17.842 --> 00:02:20.042
