64
00:03:24.695 --> 00:03:27.775
Colobomatous cleft, do you understand what it was?

65
00:03:27.775 --> 00:03:32.215
With, you see, this remnant here, then this closure that will occur.

66
00:03:32.755 --> 00:03:37.135
So the retina, in fact, is the innermost layer of the eye.

67
00:03:37.755 --> 00:03:40.475
And so, where does this retina come from?

68
00:03:42.615 --> 00:03:44.495
Do you remember this first vesicle?

69
00:03:44.565 --> 00:03:50.465
this small sphere that emerges, which we call the primary optic vesicle,

70
00:03:50.705 --> 00:03:56.065
which will make a movement like this, you see, like a

71
00:03:56.065 --> 00:03:57.045
